2_QA_QC.Rmd \
Cleaning raw urchin transect, kelp out planted plots and environmental data. Making certain variables numeric, fixing errors in data entry, create new more meaningful columns, renaming sites for alignment, removing leading/trailing zeros. For environmental data (HOBO), data was summarized based on conditions between monitoring periods. \
Creates a combined cleaned dataset for analysis and modelling, includes diversity indices, bottom ENV data, \
\
Percent kelp = number gravel with kelp / number of gravel total x 100 \
\
Urchin density (for plots) - calculated per meter squared \
	For open plots - urchin density = total number urchins / 1 \
	For caged plots - urchin density = total number urchins / 4.5 \
\
Kelp_growth = summed growth per plot \
	\
	Inputs\
	- urchin_monitoring_transects.csv  (raw data) \
	- green_gravel_monitoring.csv (raw data) \
	- YSI_measurement.csv (raw data) \
	- combined_hobo.csv (output of previous script, processed data) \
\
	Outputs \
	- cleaned_green_gravel_monitoring.csv (processed data) \
	- cleaned_monitoring_transects.csv (processed_data) \
	- cleaned_ysi_measurement.csv" (processed data) \
	- summary_hobo.csv (processed data) \
	- density_urchin_transects.csv (summary of urchin densities per transect)\
	- cleaned_data.csv (combined data frame) \
\
Notes\
- A lot of missing values in YSI data (due to sensor issues, weather contingencies) \
- Will eventually need to add tilt current meter data \
