4. Density_Models.Rmd \
\
	Perform GLMM on density data and predictors (Tweedie distribution) \
		Random effect: plot_id, site \
		Fixed effects (before stepwise selection): bottom salinity, bottom do, bottom ph, mean temperature, mean light lux, mean depth, treatment, % algae, month, site\
		Stepwise predictor selection (based on AIC) \
		Final best model : urchin_density ~ shannon_div + bottom_do + bottom_ph + mean_light_lux + mean_depth + treatment + percent_occuring_algae \
						+ (1 | site) \
\
		Create plots of model fit, CV and coefficients\
\
		Note- month + site included as fixed effect\
\
	Run a generalized linear model on site densities (Gaussian distribution) - using MASS package\
		Predictors (before stepwise selection): bottom do, bottom salinity, mean temperature, mean light lux, mean depth, species richness, \
										shannon diversity, simpson diversity (no ph due to sensor issues) \
		Stepwise predictor selection based on AIC \
		Final best model: site_density ~ mean_light_lux + bottom_do + mean_temperature + mean_depth_m + mean_light_lux + shannon_div \
 \
\
	Plot (treatment) density models - \
		- Response variable: urchin density (not logged) -\
		- Overdispersion: 2.35 (over dispersed)\
		- Zero-inflated: 40% of data is zeros \
		- Tweedie distribution\
\
	Inputs \
		- cleaned_data.csv\
\
	Outputs\
		- correlation_plot.png\
		- testDispersion_plot.png\
		- QQ_plot.png\
		- residuals_vs_predictor.png\
		- dot_and_whisker_plot.png\
		- site_testDispersion_plot.png\
		- site_QQ_plot.png\
		- site_residuals_vs_predictor.png\
\
Notes \
- when including site as random effect, KS is significant (bad model fit) \
\
