6.Kelp_Survival_Models.Rmd\
	Run GLMM with forward feature selection (Beta distribution) on kelp survival\
		Response: kelp proportion (between 0-1, adjusted with small constant)\
		Overdispersion = 0.37 (very high) \
		Zero-inflation = None (when using adjusted with small constant) \
		Random effects = site,  plot_id\
		Testing predictors (before forward feature selection): mean_temp, mean_light, mean_depth, treatment, gravel_size\
												     bottom_do, bottom_salinity, bottom_ph, simp_diversity, shannon_diversity\
												     species_richness, site_density, urchin_density\
		Final model (based on forward feature selection AIC considering collinearity: kelp_prop_adj <- month + gravel_size + simp_div + species_richness \
		Model fit is BAD so we try other model types \
	\
		Note - did not use month as predictor \
		\
					\
	Run Zero Inflated Negative Binomial GLMM\
		Response: kelp survival (as an integer) \
		Random effect: site plot_id\
		Testing predictors (before forward feature selection): mean_temp, mean_light, mean_depth, treatment, gravel_size\
												     bottom_do, bottom_salinity, bottom_ph, simp_diversity, \
												     species_richness, site_density, urchin_density\
		Forward feature selection \
		Final model: kelp survival ~ treatment + gravel_size + mean_light_lux + mean_temperature_c + site_density + urchin_density + bottom_do + simp_div + month + \
				 (1 | site) + (1+plot_id)\
\
		Note - used month as predictor \
	\
	Inputs \
		- cleaned_green_gravel_monitoring.csv\
		- cleaned_data.csv\
\
	\
	Outputs\
		- correlation_plot.png\
		- beta_testDispersion_plot.png\
